00:00:07.238 --> 00:00:09.261
today we will make namakpare.

00:00:12.299 --> 00:00:15.505
namakpare are liked by everyone.

00:00:15.690 --> 00:00:21.349
so let's see what all ingredients are required for making namakpare.

00:00:22.229 --> 00:00:23.809
maida- 2 cup

00:00:24.501 --> 00:00:27.676
oil - 1/4 cup(for kneading dough)

00:00:28.157 --> 00:00:30.815
salt - as per taste (1/2 tsp)

00:00:31.644 --> 00:00:33.834
carom seeds - 1/2 tsp

00:00:34.353 --> 00:00:36.607
oil - to fry namakpare

00:00:37.896 --> 00:00:41.665
knead dough for making namakpare first.

00:00:45.102 --> 00:00:51.415
add salt,carom seeds and oil in flour.

00:00:54.335 --> 00:00:56.612
mix all ingredients nicely.

00:01:06.022 --> 00:01:09.450
with help of water knead the flour.

00:01:16.533 --> 00:01:17.977
add little water at a time.

00:01:39.334 --> 00:01:41.620
dough should be tight like that of required for making poori.

00:01:44.045 --> 00:01:52.699
dough is ready;now keep it aside for 20 minutes so that it puffs up.

00:02:07.641 --> 00:02:11.038
take oil in pan and place it on flame for heating.

00:02:26.002 --> 00:02:31.161
for kneading this much quantity we have used less then 1/2 cup of water.

00:02:31.786 --> 00:02:33.786
divide dough into two parts.

00:02:36.362 --> 00:02:43.535
round one part and then roll it.

00:02:53.914 --> 00:02:59.969
keep it 1/4 cm thick.

00:03:09.032 --> 00:03:16.195
now we will cut it into small or big square pieces.

00:03:19.821 --> 00:03:24.035
we are making .45 inch pieces.

00:03:54.850 --> 00:04:00.256
oil is hot;palce the square in the pan.

00:04:02.792 --> 00:04:09.022
fry on low flame until they turn brown in color.

00:04:23.857 --> 00:04:26.906
meanwhile prepare rest of the namakpare.

00:04:41.361 --> 00:04:43.520
stir them like this.

00:05:03.536 --> 00:05:08.116
with this prui make thin and long pieces.

00:05:09.670 --> 00:05:14.963
cut into 1/2 cm thin pieces.

00:05:17.186 --> 00:05:20.733
cut into any shape of your choice.

00:05:49.490 --> 00:05:53.657
take out the ones fried.

00:06:19.442 --> 00:06:23.101
now place the long pieces in the pan.

00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:29.330
cut from center ito two parts.

00:06:41.689 --> 00:06:47.347
keep the flame low as they will turn crown from outisde and remain soggy from inside.

00:06:47.584 --> 00:06:52.912
fry on low flame until they get crusty and brown in color.

00:07:08.684 --> 00:07:12.970
take out the once fried.

00:07:13.189 --> 00:07:17.491
it takes  8-9 minutes in fying them.

00:07:44.799 --> 00:07:47.632
crusty namakpare are ready.

00:07:47.834 --> 00:07:53.961
to make them spicy sprinkle chaat masala on them.

00:07:54.150 --> 00:08:05.214
store them in air tight container and enjoy eating for up to 2 months.

00:08:05.487 --> 00:08:11.154
